{"id":45965,"date":"2024-01-02T10:48:16","date_gmt":"2024-01-02T05:18:16","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/?p=45965"},"modified":"2023-06-02T10:48:20","modified_gmt":"2023-06-02T05:18:20","slug":"how-to-make-small-kitchen-look-bigger","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/modular-kitchen-interiors\/how-to-make-small-kitchen-look-bigger\/","title":{"rendered":"From Cluttered to Chic: 7 Ways to Create Space in Your Small Kitchen"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>7 easy tips on how to make a small kitchen spacious<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you\u2019ve been wondering how to make a small kitchen look bigger, be ready to be surprised. You can make your kitchen space roomy very easily without doing any major renovation. Yes, a white theme does make a space look big and airy, but it\u2019s not the only way. You don\u2019t have to sacrifice colour and style to make your kitchen space look bigger. Here\u2019re 8 cool ways you can transform the heart of your home without breaking the bank.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Knock Down The Wall and Maintain a Straight Layout<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>If your kitchen has a wall that separates the living room, here\u2019s an easy tip on how to make the kitchen look bigger. Consider breaking down the divider wall. This will create an open floor plan and instantly make the space feel larger. Also, the straight kitchen layout works best for a <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/modular-kitchen-interiors\/small-kitchen-design-in-indian-style\/\">small kitchen<\/a>. It leaves a lot of space to move around. Keep in mind that decluttering and organising your space can further help create a more open and airy feel.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/06\/02103935\/make-kitchen-bigger-with-removed-divider-wall.jpg\" alt=\"Consider breaking down the divider wall to make the kitchen bigger\" class=\"wp-image-45977\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/06\/02103935\/make-kitchen-bigger-with-removed-divider-wall.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/06\/02103935\/make-kitchen-bigger-with-removed-divider-wall-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/06\/02103935\/make-kitchen-bigger-with-removed-divider-wall-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/06\/02103935\/make-kitchen-bigger-with-removed-divider-wall-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>Break down walls to make your kitchen feel bigger instantly<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"mbgc-slide-caption\"><a href=\"#contactUsModal\" data-toggle=\"modal\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"Upgrade your modular kitchen to a smart space saving solutions\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/11\/07151812\/upgrade-your-modular-kitchen-to-smart-space-saving-solutions.jpg \" \/><\/a><\/div>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Let The Sunshine and Nature In To Make A Small Kitchen Look Bigger<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Wondering how to make a small dark kitchen look brighter? A window can do the trick. The bigger, the better. You can easily transform a small kitchen space by letting the natural light and nature. Keep it free from blinds and curtains to ensure light and air are never obstructed.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/06\/02103958\/make-small-kitchen-look-brighter-with-window.jpg\" alt=\"Make a small dark kitchen look bigger by installing a large window to brighten the area\" class=\"wp-image-45982\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/06\/02103958\/make-small-kitchen-look-brighter-with-window.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/06\/02103958\/make-small-kitchen-look-brighter-with-window-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/06\/02103958\/make-small-kitchen-look-brighter-with-window-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/06\/02103958\/make-small-kitchen-look-brighter-with-window-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>Brighten up your small kitchen with a window<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Add More Open Shelves To Make Kitchen Look Bigger<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Not all of us are fortunate enough to have a spacious kitchen. So, here\u2019s an easy tip on how to make your kitchen look bigger without any significant carpentry changes. Just take the shutters off the cabinets. By doing so, you\u2019d create an innate sense of openness. Also, open shelves are on-trend now.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Like the kitchen shown in the image below. Although the kitchen is built in a tiny space under the staircase, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/modular-kitchen-interiors\/open-shelving-kitchen-ideas\/\">open shelves<\/a> have made the kitchen look spacious. So, if you are a neat and tidy person, this would stunningly work for you.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/06\/02103912\/gallery-kitchen-with-open-shelves-look-bigger.jpg\" alt=\"Add more open shelves to make your gallery kitchen look bigger\" class=\"wp-image-45971\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/06\/02103912\/gallery-kitchen-with-open-shelves-look-bigger.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/06\/02103912\/gallery-kitchen-with-open-shelves-look-bigger-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/06\/02103912\/gallery-kitchen-with-open-shelves-look-bigger-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/06\/02103912\/gallery-kitchen-with-open-shelves-look-bigger-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>Open up your kitchen space with open shelves<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Incorporate Reflective Material For An Expansive Feel<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Reflective materials in a small kitchen, such as glossy cabinets, stainless steel appliances, or mirrored backsplash, can help make the space look roomier by creating an illusion of depth and expansiveness. These materials reflect light and create a sense of openness, making the room feel brighter and larger.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>In the kitchen below, we experimented with stainless steel countertops since glass is hard to maintain. And the result is a stunning <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/modular-kitchen-interiors\/modern-sleek-kitchen-design\/\">modern and sleek kitchen<\/a> that looks and feels much bigger, thanks to the large bay window that lets a lot of natural light in.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/06\/02103942\/make-kitchen-look-bigger-and-brighter-with-reflective-surfaces.jpg\" alt=\"Kitchen with glossy cabinets, stainless steel appliances, or mirrored backsplash gives bigger look kitchen\" class=\"wp-image-45979\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/06\/02103942\/make-kitchen-look-bigger-and-brighter-with-reflective-surfaces.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/06\/02103942\/make-kitchen-look-bigger-and-brighter-with-reflective-surfaces-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/06\/02103942\/make-kitchen-look-bigger-and-brighter-with-reflective-surfaces-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/06\/02103942\/make-kitchen-look-bigger-and-brighter-with-reflective-surfaces-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>Easy tip on how to make a kitchen look bigger and brighter with reflective surfaces<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Use Cabinet Lights and See-through Shutters To Make Small Kitchen Look Brighter<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>If open shelving is not your cup of tea, the best alternative is see-through cabinet shutters. They offer a sense of expansiveness while protecting your crockeries from dust. To enhance the beauty of the space, add recessed lights inside the cabinets. Alternatively, add lights underneath the top cupboards or at the base of floor units. This creates an illusion of depth.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/06\/02103951\/make-small-kitchen-look-bigger-with-cabinet-lights.jpg\" alt=\"Add see-through cabinet shutters with lights to make a small kitchen look bigger\" class=\"wp-image-45981\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/06\/02103951\/make-small-kitchen-look-bigger-with-cabinet-lights.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/06\/02103951\/make-small-kitchen-look-bigger-with-cabinet-lights-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/06\/02103951\/make-small-kitchen-look-bigger-with-cabinet-lights-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/06\/02103951\/make-small-kitchen-look-bigger-with-cabinet-lights-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>Quick tip on how to make the kitchen bigger with cabinet lights<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"mbgc-slide-caption\"><a href=\"#contactUsModal\" data-toggle=\"modal\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"Get a Free Modular Kitchen Worth \u20b92 Lakhs with Your Home Interiors.\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/08\/08183703\/designcafe-offer-free-modular-kitchen-worth-2-lakhs.jpg \" \/><\/a><\/div>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Use Bright Colours To Make Small Kitchen Look Bigger With Paint<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>If you are looking for an easy tip on making a small kitchen look bigger with paint, your search ends here. A fresh coat of paint can instantly transform a dark, gloomy kitchen. Although the <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/modular-kitchen-interiors\/white-kitchen-designs\/\">white kitchen<\/a> is on-trend, you can choose bright colours like pink, peach, and yellow for a welcoming vibe. Furthermore, you can combine white with pastel green or teal to make the space look more airy and trendy. But remember to keep the space always uncluttered so that it feels roomy.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/06\/02103928\/how-to-make-small-kitchen-look-bigger-with-paint.jpg\" alt=\"Easy tip on how to make a kitchen look bigger with paint\" class=\"wp-image-45975\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/06\/02103928\/how-to-make-small-kitchen-look-bigger-with-paint.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/06\/02103928\/how-to-make-small-kitchen-look-bigger-with-paint-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/06\/02103928\/how-to-make-small-kitchen-look-bigger-with-paint-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/06\/02103928\/how-to-make-small-kitchen-look-bigger-with-paint-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>Changing the paint is a low-cost way to make the kitchen look bigger<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>FAQs<\/strong> <strong>on how to make a kitchen look bigger <\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>1. How do you make a small kitchen feel bigger?<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Implement the below tips to create a more open and spacious feel in your small kitchen.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><li>Maximise natural light<\/li><li>Choose light colours<\/li><li>Use open shelving<\/li><li>Get rid of clutter<\/li><li>Use multi-functional furniture<\/li><li>Create visual interest<\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>2. What colour makes a small kitchen look bigger?<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Using light colours is an easy way to make a small kitchen look bigger because they reflect more light, making the space feel more open and airy. Some of the best colours are:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><li>White<\/li><li>Light grey<\/li><li>Pale blue<\/li><li>Soft green<\/li><li>Beige or cream<\/li><li>Pastel pink<\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>3. What size tiles make a kitchen look bigger?<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>When it comes to tile size in a small kitchen, larger tiles tend to make the space feel bigger. Larger tiles can make the floor or backsplash feel more expansive and continuous. Some tile sizes that work well in a small kitchen include:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><li>12 x 24 inches<\/li><li>18 x 18 inches<\/li><li>24 x 24 inches<\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Urban subway tiles or herringbone pattern tiles work well in small spaces.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>In conclusion, a few simple changes can make a small kitchen look bigger. By implementing these tips, you can create a more open and spacious feel in your kitchen without spending lakhs. To learn more about kitchen renovation ideas or to discuss your specific needs with our interior experts, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/\">book a free consultation<\/a> call today and check out our <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/modular-kitchen-interiors\/\">blog section<\/a> 